                  <handDesc>
                     <p>Written along the fibers in medium-sized cursive and well-practiced hand. The interlinear spaces are mostly even of ca. 0.8 cm. The letters are ligatured with the characteristics of the 4th Century; the two loops alpha; a V-shaped upsilon; pi with horizontal stroke with serifs two legs; a mall circular omicron. No diacritical marks or abbreviations are attested. Verso has the name of addressee; who mentioned as �ǣmou kurio�ǥ which gives us impression that the letter is from a woman.</p>
